The article is a memorandum from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Secretary of State regarding the delegation of authority under Section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The President delegates to the Secretary of State the authority to direct the drawdown of up to $625 million in defense articles, services, military education, and training to provide assistance to Ukraine. The Secretary of State is also authorized to make the necessary determinations required for such a drawdown. The memorandum directs the Secretary of State to publish it in the Federal Register.